docs.text: " you've got mail " is the very definition of a " cute " movie .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it's got cute stars , a cute story-line , and even cute pets .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: despite this over-whelming cuteness ( or maybe because of it ) , i loved " you've got mail " .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: i know , i know .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: i'm supposed to be a film critic .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: i'm not supposed to love transparent and formula pictures like this .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but darn it , somewhere along the way , " you've got mail " reeled me in , hook , line , and sinker .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the movie stars tom hanks and meg ryan as two somewhat unhappy new yorkers who meet in an aol online chat room and quickly become close friends , without ever knowing each others identity .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: as the movie progresses , though , they begin to discover that they have a lot in common with each other .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: meanwhile , in " real-life " , they are bitter competitors .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: she owns a quaint little children's bookstore , he owns one of those gigantic super-bookstores that offer impersonal service and discount prices .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: while his store threatens to run her store out of business , their online relationship grows stronger .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: " you've got mail " is as artificial as movies come .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: everything is nice and happy and by the end , all the characters have gotten exactly what they wanted out of life .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: there are no real conflicts , no major disappointments , no unresolved issues .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: nevertheless , i quite enjoyed it .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: in fact , i can't remember the last time i had such a good time at the movies .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: i think sometimes you have to be able to watch a movie and just get drawn into it .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the fact that stars hank and ryan are at the top of their game does not hurt either .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: in particular , hanks is at his best here , turning his " charm-meter " up to 11 .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: everytime he was on screen , he had my full attention .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: and despite the fact that he was driving little bookstores out of business , i was rooting for him .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it was good to see hanks back doing what he does best : playing the affable everyman .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: " you've got mail " certainly won't be winning any awards , but as an exercise in pure entertainment , it's as good as it gets .
docs.label: positive
